refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.attributes;
Attributes for TarTask
&taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;
destfile
String
Tarball filename
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.yes;
basedir
String
Base directory to tar (if no fileset specified, entire directory contents will be included in tar)
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
compression
String
Type of compression to use (gzip, bzip2, none)
none
&attributes.required.no;
includeemptydirs
Boolean
If set to true, also empty directories are copied.
true
&attributes.required.no;
longfile
String
How to handle long files, those with a path > 100 chars. Allowable values are: truncate - paths are truncated to the maximum length; fail - paths greater than the maximim cause a build exception; warn - paths greater than the maximum cause a warning and GNU is used; gnu - GNU extensions are used for any paths greater than the maximum; omit - paths greater than the maximum are omitted from the archive
warn
&attributes.required.no;
prefix
String
File path prefix to use when adding files to archive
&attributes.defaultValue.NA;
&attributes.required.no;
Important note #1: files are not replaced if they are already present in the archive.
Important note #2: using basedir and fileset simultaneously can result in strange contents in the archive.
